    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim does not display colours when rendering output from filter command.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start clean neovim: `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Run the command `:!echo -e \"\\033[31mfoo\\033[0m\"`\r\n3. Neovim prints: \r\n  ```\r\n  :!echo -e \"\\033[31mfoo\\033[0m\"                                                                                                           \r\n    ^[[31mfoo^[[0m\r\n  ```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim prints `foo` in red.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.5 Build type: Release\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim prints colours. VIM - Vi IMproved 9.1 (2024 Jan 02, compiled Apr 18 2024 16:54:46) Included patches: 1-346\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.33.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\narch extra repository",
